    • resetReachableCells

      public void resetReachableCells(boolean state)
      Since boardifierconsole is in text mode, the default behaviour is to have no special rendering for cells that can be reached, after for example, selecting an element that should be played. This is why this method calls the general method below with a second parameter as false, to prevent a ChangeFace event to be created.
      Parameters:
      state -

    • moveElement

      public void moveElement(GameElement element, int rowDest, int colDest)
      Move an element from a grid cell to another one. This method has 2 modes to process the move: 1) removes the element from its current cell and use putElement() to assign it to the new cell. It leads to call the callbacks once again, and to set the location of the element, by default at the cell center 2) just reassign the cell that owns the element. No callbacks are called and the lcoation is not updated. Useful for moving sprites owned by a grid.
      Parameters:
      element - the element to move
      rowDest - the new grid row of the element
      colDest - the new grid column of the element

    • getElement

      public GameElement getElement(int row, int col)
      get the first element that is stored in cell row,col. It is a "convenience" method that is an alias for getFirstElement, in case of a game enforce the fact that there is no more than a single element in a cell at any time.
      Parameters:
      row - the cell row
      col - the cell col
      Returns:
      the first element stored or null if there are no elements
      See Also:
